.TH RAID-CHECK-SERIAL 8 "March 2026" "better-raid-check" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
raid-check-serial.sh \- run MD RAID checks with media-aware concurrency limits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B raid-check-serial.sh
.RI [ md-array " ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B raid-check-serial.sh
starts MD RAID check operations with separate concurrency limits for HDD,
SSD, and NVM-backed arrays.
.PP
If no array names are provided, the command auto-discovers redundant MD
arrays and schedules checks for eligible devices.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Runtime options are read from
.I /etc/default/raid-check-serial
when invoked by systemd.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/sbin/raid-check-serial.sh
Main executable.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/raid-check-serial.service
Systemd oneshot service unit.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/raid-check-serial.timer
Systemd timer unit for scheduled runs.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mdadm (8),
.BR systemd.service (5),
.BR systemd.timer (5)
